meet them before the wedding.

08:28.583 --> 08:31.283
- Where's Tom?
- Er, what?

08:31.331 --> 08:33.251
He just came in here.
Did he want to see me?

08:33.745 --> 08:35.525
I don't know.

08:35.573 --> 08:37.539
Julie, was Tom here?

08:37.682 --> 08:40.486
Erm, well, yes, he's got an appointment.

08:40.650 --> 08:42.650
- Not with me.
- Sian. He's in with Sian.

08:42.767 --> 08:44.901
- Sian's not his doctor.
- Why? Why's he in there?

08:45.017 --> 08:48.651
I don't know. And, well,
it's confidential, isn't it?

08:56.486 --> 08:59.761
- All right?
- Yeah. Thanks.

09:13.925 --> 09:15.158
Hello?

09:15.923 --> 09:17.069
Hi.

09:17.424 --> 09:18.746
What's the problem?

09:18.794 --> 09:21.065
No problem, I was... I was just
going to make myself a cup of tea,

09:21.112 --> 09:22.941
and I thought you might want to join me.

09:23.822 --> 09:24.970
Oh!

09:25.059 --> 09:26.728
It's more or less arranged,

09:26.822 --> 09:29.134
I mean, it's happening
in the next few days so...

09:29.217 --> 09:31.346
But I understand that that's
exactly why you need to

09:31.393 --> 09:34.845
plan your contingencies.
I mean, what if someone gets ill?

09:34.955 --> 09:37.644
Or what happens if you haven't
booked the venue properly?

09:37.692 --> 09:39.580
Or if something gets
on your dress? You know,

09:39.702 --> 09:42.191
I went to a wedding once
where there weren't any plates.

09:42.415 --> 09:43.924
They forgot the plates!

09:44.080 --> 09:45.876
Well, I'm sure it'll be all right.

09:45.939 --> 09:47.570
And the weather! You can't predict that!

09:47.634 --> 09:50.447
They say you can but you
can't. Weddington boots.

09:50.548 --> 09:52.784
- I'm sorry?
- Weddington boots. Wellies for a wedding.

09:52.832 --> 09:54.963
You really should have some of
those. You should go online...

09:55.011 --> 09:58.751
- I think we should be OK.
- We're indoors mostly.

09:58.832 --> 10:00.561
But you can't be too careful.

10:00.790 --> 10:03.611
My friend Esther, she
got married on a beach,

10:03.830 --> 10:05.306
and there was a hurricane.

10:06.199 --> 10:07.852
Actually,
you put the kettle on.

10:07.900 --> 10:09.228
I'll be with you in a minute.

10:09.291 --> 10:12.900
Oh.
OK. Sure.

10:15.712 --> 10:17.228
Sian! Hi!

10:17.442 --> 10:18.661
Hi!

10:21.212 --> 10:24.501
- Had a good morning?
- Yes. I didn't think you were in today.

10:24.642 --> 10:29.376
Well, I'm not, officially.
Actually, I wanted to catch you.

10:30.129 --> 10:31.783
I wondered...

10:32.689 --> 10:34.519
Do you want to come
round for dinner tonight?

10:34.566 --> 10:38.455
- Dinner? At yours? With...?
- With me.

10:38.622 --> 10:40.423
Erm, just you?

10:40.508 --> 10:42.580
Just me, yes.

10:43.228 --> 10:46.024
There's been a bit of tension
between us and I thought maybe

10:46.072 --> 10:48.603
we should get to know each
other in a less formal setting.

10:48.814 --> 10:50.773
What do you think? Are you free?

10:52.213 --> 10:54.447
Why don't you
come to mine instead?

10:54.524 --> 10:56.165
I've got a monkfish
and some asparagus.

10:56.213 --> 10:58.642
I was going to do it anyway.
Enough for two.

11:00.617 --> 11:02.790
Sure. Right.

11:03.014 --> 11:05.634
- Oh, bring wine.
- I'll bring lots.

11:06.564 --> 11:09.203
They said you weren't here
today, but it's urgent.

11:09.267 --> 11:11.142
I can't lift up my arms.

11:13.160 --> 11:14.845
Erm, Sian?

11:15.764 --> 11:17.705
Could you do me a favour?

11:52.142 --> 11:55.094
- Hi. Sorry I'm late but I got held up.
- Yeah, so let's go.

11:55.142 --> 11:57.040
You said early evenings
was better, I believe?

11:57.111 --> 11:59.728
- I don't understand.
- Shall we start inside?

12:00.009 --> 12:03.108
- Are you the taxi?
- Estate agent. Your husband called,

12:03.164 --> 12:04.814
asking for a valuation.

12:04.961 --> 12:06.447
I don't have a husband.

12:06.647 --> 12:08.392
I'm sure this is the right address.

12:08.566 --> 12:10.165
Is it Doctor Foster?

12:10.213 --> 12:12.344
The man who called you,
you still have his number?

12:12.392 --> 12:14.641
- I expect so.
- Call him back, say if he does this again,

12:14.689 --> 12:16.680
his ex-wife will contact the police.

12:21.222 --> 12:23.331
- Good luck.
- Thank you.

12:26.694 --> 12:28.103
And you.

12:29.439 --> 12:31.703
So, you don't want a valuation?

12:58.244 --> 12:59.978
- Oh.
- What?

13:00.205 --> 13:02.743
- You are expecting me?
- Well, yes, but not at this time.

13:02.814 --> 13:04.477
- You're early.
- By five minutes?

13:04.548 --> 13:05.861
Exactly. I was...

13:07.205 --> 13:09.681
It's fine. I'll manage.

13:11.689 --> 13:14.323
- Well, come on in, then.
- Thank you.

13:21.486 --> 13:23.400
- Hey!
- Sorry. Long day.

13:23.471 --> 13:24.908
It's all right.

13:25.041 --> 13:28.228
- So, er, what'll it be?
- Red Ribbon.

13:28.434 --> 13:30.496
A Red Ribbon, please.

13:30.994 --> 13:32.877
How are you coping with the pub?

13:33.002 --> 13:36.799
Yeah. Well, I'm not entirely
comfortable, as you can imagine.

13:36.963 --> 13:39.478
- I can.
- It's just so dirty.

13:39.869 --> 13:41.463
Because of all the poor people.

13:41.554 --> 13:43.806
It's good to know you haven't changed.

13:45.622 --> 13:47.921
This could be so weird. Us meeting.

13:49.341 --> 13:52.013
Yeah. Yeah, I suppose so.

13:52.251 --> 13:54.106
Ah, thank you. There you go!

13:54.801 --> 13:57.458
But, as you said, long time ago now.

13:57.661 --> 13:59.513
You've got a new wife

14:00.052 --> 14:03.145
and a big new house, by all accounts.

14:03.474 --> 14:04.853
Life carries on.

14:05.013 --> 14:08.093
Yeah, yeah. It does. For most of us.

14:10.528 --> 14:12.216
Shall we open a bottle?

14:12.264 --> 14:13.841
I actually brought a couple.

14:14.077 --> 14:18.435
Oh! Well, er, let's, er...

14:19.048 --> 14:22.557
Mmm... put these to chill,
start with one of mine.

14:22.714 --> 14:26.247
All right? There's a vineyard

14:26.442 --> 14:31.685
in Ledoc, and my half-brother
owns a stake in it,

14:32.051 --> 14:34.364
brings me these bottles back.

14:36.418 --> 14:38.484
Is that your son?

14:39.117 --> 14:42.255
Yes. He's at university now.

14:42.466 --> 14:44.457
I didn't realise you had any children.

14:45.192 --> 14:47.032
Harry is
the product of an unhappy

14:47.094 --> 14:49.224
and short-lived relationship
with a man called Evan.

14:49.394 --> 14:52.443
Evan had issues, which, when we
were younger, appeared to be charm

14:52.491 --> 14:56.044
and ambition, but, as he got
older, were revealed to be

14:56.231 --> 14:57.790
bitterness and aggression.

14:59.269 --> 15:00.358
Cheers.

15:01.278 --> 15:02.731
Does Harry see much of him?

15:02.801 --> 15:04.255
Not if I can help it.

15:04.488 --> 15:06.227
His dad's a shit.

15:07.942 --> 15:09.220
Harry is amazing.

15:09.268 --> 15:11.942
And it's precisely
because I kept them apart.

15:12.536 --> 15:14.911
What about you? You're
divorced. How's your son?

15:15.247 --> 15:19.177
He's... fine. I think.

15:20.407 --> 15:22.317
And do you see much of his dad?

15:24.458 --> 15:25.841
No.

15:25.899 --> 15:30.239
Yeah, big house, big
mortgage, but it's worth it.

15:30.739 --> 15:33.652
But, after everything that happened,
how... how can you afford it?

15:36.192 --> 15:38.058
- What?
- You've not been the most

15:38.138 --> 15:39.419
discreet person in the past.

15:39.491 --> 15:41.270
Well, I was led astray.

15:41.341 --> 15:44.661
- And how do I know it won't happen again?
- With Gemma?

15:46.352 --> 15:47.661
Once was enough.

15:49.841 --> 15:53.614
OK, well, the truth is Kate's
dad gave us a few thousand.

15:53.684 --> 15:56.356
Then a mate had a tip-off in
an American energy company,

15:56.497 --> 15:58.825
fracking, whatever. It doesn't matter.

15:58.880 --> 16:00.950
The point is we invested what we could,

16:01.031 --> 16:04.442
and within a year,
I mean, wow!

16:04.599 --> 16:06.370
- You did well?
- Unbelievable.

16:06.419 --> 16:07.770
Ah.

16:07.903 --> 16:09.930
You... you liked it? The space?

16:09.989 --> 16:11.085
- Yeah.
- Yeah, small businesses

16:11.132 --> 16:14.270
love the idea of a shared ethos.

16:14.653 --> 16:18.177
And the community café acts
as a... as a hub which...

16:19.193 --> 16:20.731
Distracted?

16:21.191 --> 16:23.763
What? No.

16:24.161 --> 16:26.911
No, I am past all that now.

16:27.903 --> 16:29.492
Happily married.

16:33.125 --> 16:34.825
What was she like?

16:35.861 --> 16:37.920
My wife, when you slept with her?

16:39.700 --> 16:43.177
I... mate...

16:43.475 --> 16:44.924
Did you have fun?

16:46.081 --> 16:47.778
Yeah, we did.

16:48.230 --> 16:49.761
But you wouldn't go there again?

16:52.270 --> 16:54.753
Like tequila. Great at the time.

16:54.888 --> 16:56.250
Not worth the hangover.

16:56.360 --> 16:57.859
Tequila!

16:59.596 --> 17:01.716
Did she strip off at the end of the bed?

17:02.817 --> 17:04.881
She likes to slowly take her
clothes off in front of you.

17:04.928 --> 17:06.560
It's a thing she does.
Turns her on.

17:07.791 --> 17:11.339
- You really want to know?
- Good body, right? For her age.

17:11.480 --> 17:14.260
I suppose. Yeah, great body.

17:14.409 --> 17:17.089
She used to tense. You're
right in the middle of it,

17:17.330 --> 17:20.089
and she... she'd come and get
these, like, electric shocks,

17:20.221 --> 17:22.721
all the way through her body,
right in the middle of fucking.

17:22.987 --> 17:25.010
I miss that. Did she do that?

17:25.171 --> 17:26.443
You would remember.

17:26.690 --> 17:28.455
I'm not sure I want to
share that information.

17:28.502 --> 17:31.354
"Don't want to share."
You used to over share.

17:31.487 --> 17:33.057
Every time I saw you we were
supposed to be talking about

17:33.104 --> 17:36.268
investment options and you'd be
explaining what a butter churner was.

17:38.526 --> 17:40.265
Bet you tried it.

17:42.649 --> 17:44.354
Nearly broke my neck.

17:47.581 --> 17:49.880
Well, 
I'm a very different man now.

17:54.307 --> 17:55.378
Another?

17:55.501 --> 17:56.860
Sure.

18:01.378 --> 18:03.620
- Did it in the middle of a field.
- Sorry?

18:03.768 --> 18:07.667
I mean the wedding!
Oh, God! Oh, God! No! Not sex. Never.

18:07.862 --> 18:10.460
Evan told me very early on he
didn't like sex in "weird places".

18:10.518 --> 18:12.885
I wanted to do it in a
car once and he was like,

18:12.967 --> 18:15.677
"No, it's dangerous."
I asked him why.

18:15.725 --> 18:17.677
He said, "What if you
knocked the handbrake off?

18:17.725 --> 18:19.607
Grabbed it by accident
in the throes of passion."

18:19.655 --> 18:22.490
I said, "If your penis
feels like a handbrake

18:22.581 --> 18:24.779
we have got bigger problems"!

18:26.358 --> 18:28.177
What about you? Any strange places?

18:28.321 --> 18:31.410
We did it in a castle
once. My ex and me.

18:31.513 --> 18:34.130
- Sorry?
- Castles. He liked castles.

18:34.178 --> 18:35.373
Oh, geek.

18:35.427 --> 18:37.156
I didn't mind them, actually.

18:37.310 --> 18:38.683
We were at this one by the sea,

18:38.732 --> 18:40.654
and they were kicking
everyone out, so we hid.

18:40.702 --> 18:42.826
And then we fucked each
other in the battlements.

18:46.411 --> 18:49.770
After Evan, I never had
sex with another man.

18:50.086 --> 18:53.247
- Really?
- Too messy. Women all the way.

18:53.421 --> 18:55.325
I tell you, it's better.

18:56.825 --> 18:58.374
You were married how long?

18:58.461 --> 18:59.669
15 years.

18:59.821 --> 19:01.403
And you divorced?

19:02.088 --> 19:03.867
For two years.

19:04.118 --> 19:06.005
Something they don't tell you.

19:06.241 --> 19:10.012
That indent on your finger,
where you had the ring?

19:11.967 --> 19:13.512
It never goes.

19:16.972 --> 19:18.887
Why did my son come to see you?

19:20.665 --> 19:22.411
You saw him leave.
I thought so.

19:22.459 --> 19:23.482
Why was he there?

19:23.530 --> 19:25.442
Yes.
You know I can't tell you.

19:25.588 --> 19:27.645
I know but I thought
since we were drunk...

19:27.693 --> 19:29.332
I'm not drunk.

19:29.903 --> 19:32.372
Could you at least explain
why he went to see you,

19:32.434 --> 19:33.512
and not his own doctor?

19:33.591 --> 19:35.870
Cos his own doctor is
one of your best friends.

19:36.005 --> 19:37.309
So, why you?

19:37.421 --> 19:39.044
He knew we weren't close.

19:39.092 --> 19:40.201
How?

19:40.249 --> 19:41.833
You told him I was impossible.

19:41.881 --> 19:43.167
I don't think you're impossible.

19:43.215 --> 19:44.963
- You do.
- A little difficult perhaps.

19:45.011 --> 19:47.270
- I think you're impossible.
- Unbelievably competitive.

19:47.318 --> 19:48.864
- You're smug.
- I'm glad I came for dinner.

19:48.911 --> 19:50.762
- Did you like the fish?
- No.

19:50.919 --> 19:54.536
Look, Tom suddenly went
to live with his dad

19:54.787 --> 19:57.416
and his dad is a very bad influence.

19:57.677 --> 20:00.356
Now, on top of all that,
I'm worried that he might not be well.

20:00.409 --> 20:01.808
But if you won't tell me...

20:03.199 --> 20:04.788
I get it.

20:05.031 --> 20:06.317
You're a professional.

20:06.445 --> 20:08.270
It's... it's good.

20:09.530 --> 20:11.029
It actually is.

20:11.286 --> 20:12.950
Principles.

20:13.389 --> 20:14.988
I like that.

20:19.841 --> 20:22.817
There is something
you don't know about me.

20:23.504 --> 20:25.841
Despite being a doctor,

20:26.872 --> 20:29.310
when I drink...

20:34.155 --> 20:35.466
I smoke.

20:39.069 --> 20:40.808
So what are you going to do about Gemma?

20:41.192 --> 20:42.896
She thinks you're
scheming to make her leave

20:42.943 --> 20:45.481
and she doesn't understand
why Tom's moved in with you.

20:47.566 --> 20:50.795
- Why has he moved in with you?
- It's sad, isn't it?

20:52.292 --> 20:55.778
I take responsibility for everything
I've done, but I mean, two years?

20:56.716 --> 20:59.216
