- Oh! Gemma.

49:57.840 --> 49:59.561
I was just finishing up with Mr Ward...

49:59.663 --> 50:00.820
Gordon, could you give us a moment?

50:00.867 --> 50:02.684
She's about to tell me what's wrong.

50:02.741 --> 50:04.428
- Honestly, I just...
- Doctor Lambert

50:04.476 --> 50:07.449
will finish up properly in a moment,
if you just step outside.

50:15.265 --> 50:17.374
You missed dessert,
did I do something wrong?

50:17.422 --> 50:18.819
I checked your CV.

50:19.124 --> 50:23.631
Simon, my ex-husband, did
economics at Warwick, same year.

50:23.831 --> 50:25.088
You know him.

50:25.366 --> 50:27.054
I don't think so.
I don't remember any Simons.

50:27.101 --> 50:29.710
That wasn't a question.
You know him.

50:30.778 --> 50:35.217
He said he'd spoken to some old friends,
but it was you, wasn't it?

50:35.311 --> 50:37.358
- Talking about me.
- Gemma, I can't...

50:37.406 --> 50:40.319
I could find out.
I could go on Facebook, check records.

50:40.987 --> 50:44.190
I don't take well to
people who lie to me.

50:44.743 --> 50:46.712
You can guess why.

50:48.925 --> 50:50.728
All right, yes.

50:50.913 --> 50:54.008
I know him from university
but not well.

50:54.217 --> 50:58.264
The job came up, he lived nearby,
and I asked him about the area.

50:58.402 --> 51:03.163
He said I should go for it, but
that his ex-wife was the senior GP,

51:03.381 --> 51:05.062
wouldn't take it well if
I mentioned the connection,

51:05.109 --> 51:07.756
and that she was leaving soon
anyway so there wasn't any point...

51:07.804 --> 51:09.874
- Leaving?
- Yes, he said within a month

51:10.022 --> 51:11.382
of him moving back,
you'd be gone.

51:11.441 --> 51:13.398
So you want my job,
you're working with him to get rid of me?

51:13.445 --> 51:14.780
- Don't be ridiculous.
- It's not!

51:14.828 --> 51:16.007
Because you've been reporting back

51:16.054 --> 51:17.375
- to my ex-husband...
- No, no, no!

51:17.422 --> 51:18.726
On everything that I've been doing.

51:18.773 --> 51:20.030
I have not been reporting back.

51:20.078 --> 51:22.764
He calls and asks and
I tell him the truth.

51:22.869 --> 51:24.080
- Get out.

51:24.143 --> 51:26.103
- Er, being friends with your 
boss's ex isn't,

51:26.151 --> 51:27.523
as far as I know, 
grounds for dismissal.

51:27.570 --> 51:29.210
You don't need to work any notice.

51:29.397 --> 51:34.686
Gem... Gemma, we didn't get on,
so maybe I wasn't hugely positive

51:34.734 --> 51:38.697
about you with Simon to begin with,
but I always told him the truth.

51:38.998 --> 51:41.881
And now that I've got to know
you, especially what I found out

51:41.929 --> 51:46.682
yesterday, well, it's clear,
you're not the one with the problem.

51:48.225 --> 51:49.319
Really?

51:49.444 --> 51:54.210
Yes. Look, Gemma, last night
you wanted to know about Tom.

51:54.258 --> 51:56.787
I wanted to know about you.
Now I do.

51:57.483 --> 51:59.944
You're a good person
and an excellent doctor.

52:00.530 --> 52:02.522
I hugely respect you.

52:02.999 --> 52:07.271
And that's why in the end
I told you about Tom and not him.

52:08.345 --> 52:10.545
After everything you said...

52:11.040 --> 52:13.163
I get what you're up against.

52:14.359 --> 52:16.249
And, well...

52:16.494 --> 52:20.592
I very rarely feel the
need to apologise but...

52:22.776 --> 52:24.275
sorry.

52:33.814 --> 52:35.503
So, what now?

52:54.074 --> 52:56.563
- Drink, madam?
- No, thanks.

53:00.895 --> 53:02.904
I'm so sorry, could you
excuse me for a moment?

53:03.549 --> 53:04.998
Not here.

53:25.249 --> 53:27.382
- Tom's coming home.
- Tom is home.

53:27.430 --> 53:29.363
You've told him something.
Lied to him.

53:29.429 --> 53:31.304
Why would you think that?
Because he's suddenly changed

53:31.351 --> 53:34.428
- and it doesn't make sense.
- Well, now he's got all the facts.

53:35.725 --> 53:37.034
What does that mean?

53:41.255 --> 53:42.789
You look better than
when I last saw you.

53:42.836 --> 53:45.584
I hope you had a good night.
What was it you wanted to say?

53:45.836 --> 53:48.240
You shouted last night you
had something to tell me.

53:48.389 --> 53:49.636
You know Sian.

53:50.001 --> 53:51.614
You told her to apply for the job.

53:51.755 --> 53:54.257
She saw it and asked me,
I thought it was a good opportunity...

53:54.304 --> 53:56.951
You said when you came back
that I'd be gone within a month.

53:57.224 --> 53:58.597
You will be.

53:59.428 --> 54:01.644
What's your house worth
in the end? Did they say?

54:03.707 --> 54:05.647
There is something I could tell you,

54:05.838 --> 54:07.148
- that I know.
- Go ahead.

54:07.225 --> 54:09.381
- It would hurt you.
- Go on, then.

54:10.505 --> 54:12.061
I was watching your house last night

54:12.109 --> 54:14.142
and saw Kate with a man that wasn't you.

54:14.314 --> 54:16.587
Mark's her godfather.
Anything else?

54:22.675 --> 54:24.084
Go home...

54:25.518 --> 54:27.623
pack your things, and leave.

54:28.345 --> 54:31.420
You're going to go away again and Tom...

54:32.725 --> 54:34.542
Tom's going to come back 
and live with me.

54:34.605 --> 54:35.669
Or what?

54:35.717 --> 54:38.295
Or I'll go to the lenders that
you've borrowed money from and

54:38.376 --> 54:41.299
inform them of your mismanagement
of your previous business.

54:41.412 --> 54:42.754
The "lenders".

54:43.717 --> 54:46.764
Yeah. Did Neil get home
all right in the morning?

54:46.935 --> 54:49.115
She was very attractive.
I hope they had a good time.

54:49.163 --> 54:51.787
You wanted him to go off with her.
You knew that he promised Anna...

54:51.834 --> 54:53.575
What Neil does is entirely up to him.

54:53.623 --> 54:55.450
But on the other hand,
yes, of course.

54:55.971 --> 54:57.434
He slept with my wife.

55:03.490 --> 55:06.439
I really think you need to
see someone professional now.

55:10.891 --> 55:12.390
Your eye's twitching.

55:25.708 --> 55:26.877
Yes?

55:29.046 --> 55:30.545
He's...?

55:32.248 --> 55:34.755
- Yes, of course. 20 minutes.
- Who's that?

55:34.916 --> 55:36.763
- It doesn't matter.
- Is it about Tom?

56:07.124 --> 56:08.543
Was that what you wanted to tell me?

56:08.590 --> 56:10.124
That you knew how I got the money,

56:10.172 --> 56:12.202
the investment in the American company?

56:13.592 --> 56:15.561
You didn't believe it, did you?

56:16.045 --> 56:17.278
Fracking?

56:18.300 --> 56:21.304
I thought you probably sent him
after me. Just turning up like that?

56:21.453 --> 56:24.907
Not convincing. Fun night,
though. Compared notes on you.

56:24.955 --> 56:26.443
- He said you weren't bad.
- Really?

56:26.494 --> 56:27.579
For your age.

56:34.000 --> 56:35.893
- Tom?
- Mate...

56:36.492 --> 56:37.963
Tom's been in a fight.

56:38.039 --> 56:40.009
Mr Foster, perhaps you'd
like to take a seat.

56:40.086 --> 56:41.109
- Mum, I'm fine.
- Gemma.

56:41.186 --> 56:42.186
What happened?

56:42.234 --> 56:45.241
Well, we say a fight,
but from what witnesses are saying,

56:45.289 --> 56:46.577
it was more like an attack.

56:46.625 --> 56:47.782
Who attacked him?

56:47.830 --> 56:49.296
He attacked another boy.

56:49.354 --> 56:50.611
Max Gosford.

56:50.790 --> 56:53.062
We're going to wait to
speak to Max's parents to see

56:53.110 --> 56:54.726
whether they want to
involve the police.

56:54.803 --> 56:56.195
- Mate...
- Let her finish.

56:56.243 --> 56:58.867
But for now Tom's immediately excluded.

56:59.980 --> 57:02.599
So he needs to go home
straight away. All right?

57:02.676 --> 57:04.009
Yes.

